	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Office of the Jewish Messenger</placeName>&#44;</p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>119 West Houston Street</placeName>.</p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>&#44; <date>Aug. 7. 1864</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. I. Leeser</addressee>&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Esteemed Sir&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName>M. Crehange</persName> a<lb/> member of the central committee of the<lb/> &#8220;Universal Israelite Alliance&#8221; is<lb/> in <placeName>New York</placeName> on a brief visit and has<lb/> requested me to furnish him such<lb/> statistical matter&#44; reports&#44; &#38;c. relative<lb/> to the Israelites of the <placeName>United States</placeName><lb/> as might prove of interest &#38; value to<lb/> the archives of the Alliance.<lb/>  May I ask that you will kindly<lb/> forward to me &#40;this week&#44; if possible&#44;<lb/> as <persName>Mr Crehange</persName> leaves about the <date>17th</date>.&#41;<lb/> any documents of this character con<lb/>cerning the Israelites of <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>&#44;<lb/> such as reports of the Education Society&#44;<lb/> Foster Home&#44; &#38;c.</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
			<p rend="indent(1)">It is greatly to be regretted that<lb/> a session of the Board of Delegates<lb/> is again rendered impracticable this<lb/> summer&#44; by the presence of war and<lb/> the difficulty of communicating<lb/> with members of the Board.  I<lb/> presume all that the committee<lb/> can do is to continue acting&#44; should occasion demand it&#44; and do all<lb/> in its power for the promotion of<lb/> the objects of the Board.  I had<lb/> expected the receipt of a document<lb/> you proposed drafting &#38; forwarding<lb/> to the <placeName>N. Y.</placeName> members for signature<lb/> so that congregations throughout the<lb/> Union may be reminded of the<lb/> duty of sending delegates&#59; but I<lb/> suppose you considered it inopportune<lb/> and therefore delayed its preparation.<lb/>  Any request you have to make of<lb/> me with reference to the Board<lb/> will be readily &#38; cheerfully acted</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>upon.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">If I mistake not&#44; I am<lb/> still indebted to you in the sum<lb/> of &#36;6. for the unbound Bible<lb/> sent me last <date>May</date>.  Please<lb/> find it enclosed.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">How do you progress with <persName>Miss<lb/> Aguilar&#39;s</persName> works&#59; will not the<lb/> first volume soon appear&#63;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Trusting you will kindly assist<lb/> me in procuring the desired<lb/> documents for the &#8220;Alliance&#8221;&#44;<lb/> I am&#44; dear sir&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Very Truly Yours&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">M J Isaacs</persName>.</p>
		</body>
